# UI: Base UI, not Radix

The package is `@base-ui/react`. Radix is not installed. Do not reach for
`@radix-ui/*` or `@base-ui-components/react` (an abandoned pre-1.0 name).

- **No `asChild`.** Compose with `render`: `<DropdownMenuTrigger render={<Button />} />`.
- **`DropdownMenuLabel` must be wrapped in `DropdownMenuGroup`.** Base UI maps it to
  `Menu.GroupLabel`, which throws `MenuGroupContext is missing` if it is not inside a
  `Group` — and that error takes the whole page down through the error boundary.
- Style hooks are `data-open:` / `data-closed:` / `data-checked:` — not
  `data-[state=open]:`. These variants come from `@import "shadcn/tailwind.css"` in
  `src/styles/globals.css`; do not remove that import.
- `Select`'s `onValueChange` yields `string | null`.
- Prefer **controlled** inputs (`value` + `onChange`). An uncontrolled Base UI `Input`
  outside a `Field` does not reliably fire `onChange`.

## Forms

`form.tsx` no longer exists — it is retired upstream. Build forms with `Field` +
`FieldGroup` + `@tanstack/react-form`. Valibot schemas go straight into `validators`
via Standard Schema; there is no resolver package.

## RTL

Arabic ships in this app. Use **logical properties only**: `ps-*`/`pe-*`,
`ms-*`/`me-*`, `start-*`/`end-*`, `text-start`. Never `pl-*`, `ml-*`, `left-*`,
`text-left`.

Use `size-4` rather than `h-4 w-4`.

## Accessibility

Every interactive control needs an accessible name, and it must be **unique on the
page** — two controls sharing a name is a real bug (screen readers and tests both
break on it).
